LINE.Text: What difference does breast screening make?
Cancer is unpredictable, so it's not
possible to know how a woman's
cancer would have grown had it
If we look at 1,000 women over 20 years
If they were not screened, 58 would be diagnosed with breast cancer
37 are treated and survive their disease
With screening; 75 are diagnosed with breast cancer
59 are treated and survive their disease
This many women are treated for
breast cancers that are real, but would
not have caused them any harm
So, breast screening saves lives, but causes some
women to be treated who didn't need to be
On balance, Cancer Research UK recommend that
women go for breast screening when invited
